rdcore director and actor, [[Pierre Woodman]]. \"They offered me a lead role right away as they said I had star quality\", she said. \"I am the kind of person who tries everything once. Everyone was so kind to me. I thought that if this is the situation, why not try it?\".<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web|url=http://www.budapestsun.com/news/54577 |title=Not just another Barbie - XpatLoop.com - Budapest sun archive |publisher=Budapestsun.com |date=2002-07-25 |accessdate=2013-05-22}}</ref> In 2015, Monique Cov\u00e9t was described in the film ''Best of Private 50th Anniversary'' as one of the five most legendary and formative porn actresses of the past 50 years.\n\n== Personal life ==\nCov\u00e9t has stated that she is bisexual. Details of her life and career are featured in the book [https://www.betterworldbooks.com/product/detail/Hungarian-Female-Adult-Models--Monique-Covet--Eve-Angel--Zsanett-Egerhazi--Anita-Dark--Nikki-Anderson-9781158400218 Hungarian Female Adult Models.]\n\n==Awards==\n* 1998 [[Private Media Group|Private]] Girl of the Year Award\n* 2000 [[Venus Award]] Best Actress Eastern Europe\n* 2001 [[Venus Award]] Winner Best Actress Europe\n* 2001 Zeus Award in Switzerland\n* 2002 Sexhajon dij \n* 2004 [[Brussels International Festival of Eroticism|Brussels Erotic Film Festival]] European X Awards - Lifetime Achievement Award\n* 2004 Sexiest Porn Actress \n* 2005 [https://index.hu/gal/2/pic.php?dir=0605/velvet/porno/&pid=22 Magyar Porn Oscar]  [https://index.hu/gal/2/pic.php?dir=0605/velvet/porno/&pid=24 Best Actress]\n* 2005 and 2006 Lifetime Achievement Awards \n* 2006 Hardest sex award\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Sister project links |wikt=no |commons=Monique Covet |b=no |n=no |q=no |s=no |v=no |species=no }}\n\n* {{official website|http://www.moniquecovet.eu}}\n* {{IMDb name|0133649|Monique Cov\u00e9t}}\n* {{iafd name|id=MCancellieri|gender=female|name=Monique Cov\u00e9t}}\n* {{Egafd name|m0266|Monique Cov\u00e9t}}\n* {{