{"title_page": "Habibar Rahman", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Md. Habibar Rahman\n|office      = Member of Parliament - [[Bogra-5]]\n|term_start  = 2008 \u2013 Running\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Golam Mohammad Siraj]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1945|01|31}}<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/index.php/en/get-involved/contact-an-mp?layout=edit&id=3629|title=Constituency 40_11th_En|agency=parliament.gov.bd|date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|birth_place = [[Dhunat Upazila|Dhunat]], Bogra\n|residence = [[Bogra]]\n|nationality = {{BAN}}\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Bangladesh Awami League]]\n}}\n\n'''Habibar Rahman''' ({{lang-bn|[[:bn:\u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8|\u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8]]}}; born 31 January 1945)<ref name=\":0\"/> is a [[Bangladesh Awami League]] politician and the incumbent Member of Parliament from [[Bogra-5]].<ref name=\":0\"/> He was elected as a Member of Parliament in 2018 as a candidate of Bangladesh Awami League.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md Habibar Rahman MP led an election rally in favour of ruling Awami League |url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/191531/sherpur-bogura--md--habibar-rahman-mp-led-an-election-rally--in-favour-of-ruling-awami-league-at-sherpur-town-on-sunday.html|website= thedailynewnation.com |accessdate=22 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRahman was passed HSC in 1962 from [[Government Azizul Haque College]]. He was then admitted to the [[Rajshahi University]] of Economics, one of the best scholars in the country for higher education. He has a B.A. and a M.A. degree. After completing his studies, he joined the Civil Service Police.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md. Habibar Rahman -\u09ae\u09cb\u0983 \u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 Biography |url=https://amarmp.com/mp/92/biography |website=Amarmp |accessdate=16 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=AL candidates |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangladesh-national-election-2018/awami-league-candidates-all-over-bangladesh-1670809 |accessdate=16 December 2018 |work=The Daily Star |date=8 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRahman was elected to Parliament from [[Bogra-5]] on 5 January 2014 as a Bangladesh Awami League candidate. He is an agriculture-based businessman and retired police officer. Rahman is actively involved in politics. He is the third elected member of parliament.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md. Habibar Rahman -\u09ae\u09cb\u0983 \u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 History |url=https://amarmp.com/mp/92/history |website=Amarmp |accessdate=16 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rahman, Habibar}}\n[[Category:Bangladesh Awami League politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:10th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:11th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:9th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi politicians]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi politician}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Md. Habibar Rahman\n|office      = Member of Parliament - [[Bogra-5]]\n|term_start  = 2008 \u2013 Running\n|term_end    = \n|predecessor = [[Golam Mohammad Siraj]]\n|successor   = \n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1945|01|31}}<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.parliament.gov.bd/index.php/en/get-involved/contact-an-mp?layout=edit&id=3629|title=Constituency 40_11th_En|agency=parliament.gov.bd|date=2019-10-22}}</ref>\n|birth_place = [[Dhunat Upazila|Dhunat]], Bogra\n|residence = [[Bogra]]\n|nationality = {{BAN}}\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|party       = [[Bangladesh Awami League]]\n}}\n\n'''Habibar Rahman''' ({{lang-bn|[[:bn:\u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8|\u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8]]}}; born 31 January 1945)<ref name=\":0\"/> is a [[Bangladesh Awami League]] politician and the incumbent Member of Parliament from [[Bogra-5]].<ref name=\":0\"/> He was elected as a Member of Parliament in 2018 as a candidate of Bangladesh Awami League.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md Habibar Rahman MP led an election rally in favour of ruling Awami League |url=http://thedailynewnation.com/news/191531/sherpur-bogura--md--habibar-rahman-mp-led-an-election-rally--in-favour-of-ruling-awami-league-at-sherpur-town-on-sunday.html|website= thedailynewnation.com |accessdate=22 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nRahman was passed HSC in 1962 from [[Government Azizul Haque College]]. He was then admitted to the [[Rajshahi University]] of Economics, one of the best scholars in the country for higher education. He has a B.A. and a M.A. degree. After completing his studies, he joined the Civil Service Police.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md. Habibar Rahman -\u09ae\u09cb\u0983 \u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 Biography |url=https://amarmp.com/mp/92/biography |website=Amarmp |accessdate=16 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=AL candidates |url=https://www.thedailystar.net/bangladesh-national-election-2018/awami-league-candidates-all-over-bangladesh-1670809 |accessdate=16 December 2018 |work=The Daily Star |date=8 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nRahman was elected to Parliament from [[Bogra-5]] on 5 January 2014 as a Bangladesh Awami League candidate. He is a agriculture based businessman and retired police officer. Rahman is actively involved in politics. He is the third elected member of parliament.<ref>{{cite web |title=Md. Habibar Rahman -\u09ae\u09cb\u0983 \u09b9\u09be\u09ac\u09bf\u09ac\u09b0 \u09b0\u09b9\u09ae\u09be\u09a8 History |url=https://amarmp.com/mp/92/history |website=Amarmp |accessdate=16 December 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rahman, Habibar}}\n[[Category:Bangladesh Awami League politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1945 births]]\n[[Category:10th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:11th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:9th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi politicians]]\n\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Worldbruce", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: a agriculture \u2192 an agriculture", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habibar_Rahman"}
